Yujin Zhang is a Ph.D. candidate in the Department of Political Science at Columbia University. I am interested in how individuals' political attitudes and behaviors are shaped by personal experiences, particularly their economic backgrounds. My research focuses on the political consequences of changing economic conditions, particularly those related to international trade, immigration, and economic crises.
<a href= "https://www.yujinzhang.com/">Personal Website</a>
